  fiber: 12 g
  sodium: 2080 mg
course: main course
time required: 45 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/crispy-southwest-cauliflower-taco-bar-627a6dd7c8ba6ded9d09997a
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry produce. Trim and thinly slice @radishes{3%unit}. Zest and quarter @lime{2%unit}. Roughly chop @cilantro{¼%ounce}. Cut @cauliflower florets{10%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Drain @corn kernels{13.4%ounce}, then pat very dry with #paper towels{}.

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{¾%cup}, 1¼ cups water, and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, in a #medium microwave-safe bowl{}, combine @red cabbage and carrot mix{4%ounce}, radishes, juice from one lime, 1 tsp @sugar{1.5%teaspoon}, a big pinch of salt, and @pepper{}. Cover tightly with #plastic wrap{} and microwave for ~{30%seconds}. Set aside, stirring occasionally, until ready to serve.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @smoky red pepper crema{2%tablespoon}, half the @mayonnaise{4%tablespoon}, ¼ tsp @southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon}, and ¼ tsp sugar. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over high heat. Add corn; cook, stirring, until golden brown and lightly charred in spots, ~{3-5%minutes}. (TIP: If corn starts to pop, cover pan and shake to toss.) Turn off heat; transfer to a #second medium bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

Add @hot sauce{1%teaspoon}, half the cilantro, half the lime zest, remaining mayonnaise, ½ tsp @fajita spice blend{1%tablespoon}, ¼ tsp sugar, and a squeeze of lime juice to bowl with corn. Stir to combine; season with salt and pepper.

In a #third medium bowl{}, whisk together @tempura batter{82%g}, remaining Southwest Spice, remaining Fajita Spice, ⅓ cup cold water, and a pinch of salt and pepper. Stir cauliflower into batter until fully coated.

> TIP: If needed, add more water 1 TBSP at a time until it reaches a pancake-batter-like consistency.

Heat ⅓-inch layer of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large heavy-bottomed pan{} over medium-high heat. Once oil is hot enough that a drop of batter sizzles when added to the pan, working in batches, use #tongs{} to add coated cauliflower to pan in an even layer. Cook until golden brown and crisp, ~{2-3%minutes} per side.

> TIP: Lower heat to medium if cauliflower begins to brown too quickly.

Using a #slotted spoon{}, transfer cauliflower to a paper-towel-lined #plate{}. Season with salt.

Wrap @flour tortillas{6%unit} in damp #paper towels{}. Microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in remaining cilantro, remaining lime zest, 1 TBSP @butter{1%tablespoon}, and a squeeze of lime juice. Season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: The rice is delicious as a side dish or taco filler!

Add @Monterey Jack cheese{¼%cup} to bowl with corn esquites; toss to combine.

Serve cauliflower, corn esquites, rice, tortillas, red pepper crema, and remaining lime wedges in separate bowls or plates for a build-your-own taco bar!